text: - I love the startup-type mentality.
Everyone's in, all hands on deck,

we're all passionate
about what we're doing
and doing the best for our customers.
- The most exciting part of my job
is delivering transformation hand-in-hand
with our customers and partners,
and seeing the huge impact
that our technology has for them.
- What we're doing is cutting edge,
and it's exciting.
And there's a good culture around it

and a good network of
people that can help you.

- I've just done things I
never thought I would do.
It's kind of hard to explain.

I sometimes summarize it when
I talk to people and say,
"I think I'm about two inches taller
than when I first started."
- What attracted me to AWS,
I would honestly say,
the diversity here.
Being an African American woman,

this is probably the first
company I've ever worked for
where leadership actually looks like me.

- Inclusion, Diversity, and
Equity is important to AWS
because it brings together individuals,
groups, and communities.
ID&E creates a culture
where unique perspectives, experiences,
and opinions are valued, respected,
and can be authentically expressed.
- We put our technical people
at the forefront of what we do.
As a salesperson,

I think it's great that
I get to stand back
and watch these wonderful people work
on a day-to-day basis.

- One of the things
that I really appreciate
is just being able to be candid
and to have those open conversations,
from your managers to your peers,

and really get the support
that you need throughout.
- For the most exciting part of my job

is that it requires a
high level of creativity

and comes with a high
degree of independence.

There is also a very
flexible culture here,
which means I can spend important time
with my family doing the things we love.
- Oh, I love it. It's really exciting.
It's a new challenge every single day.
